caption:
Leave a legacy, not a trace â›°ï¸

We all have a role to play to treat the great outdoors with respect, so we can return to the same beautiful spot again. When we are not mindful of our impact, the places we love can be significantly damaged for ourselves and future generations.

Hereâ€™s how to safeguard our beautiful lands, from the @nationalparkservice on its 7 Leave No Trace Principles:
- Plan ahead and prepare
- Travel and camp on durable surfaces
- Dispose of waste properly
- Leave what you find
- Minimize campfire impacts
- Respect wildlife
- Be considerate of other visitors
There is a beautiful world to explore - letâ€™s do it with the respect nature deserves!
#leavenotrace

caption:
Weâ€™re so happy to see the world opening back up again, but we canâ€™t celebrate the joy of travel without bringing awareness to the complexities our queer community faces when traveling. 

We love to travel because it gives us the chance to experience different cultures, people, perspectives + places. However, for queer travelers, safety is a big concern. In 70+ countries homosexuality is still criminalized and even punishable by death in parts of the world (USA today). A recent survey commissioned by Orbitz, found that more than a quarter of 2,000 queer Americans polled said they feel the need to downplay their identity while traveling.
